    "analysis": "We computed global P95 per (cmdb_id,kpi_name) across the full metric.csv and then checked the incident window (2020-05-31 02:30–03:00+08). Many (cmdb_id,kpi) breached their global P95 during the window. Top severity breaches include db_011 (LFParaWrite_Per_Sec, LFSync_Per_Sec), os_018 (Disk_await), db_002 (Physical_Read_Per_Sec, Logic_Read_Per_Sec), db_003 (Session_pct, DbTime, Sess_Active), and docker_008 (container_cpu_used). The largest relative deviations are db_011 LFParaWrite (severity ~126x) and os_018 Disk_await (~88x). According to the workflow, the next step is fault identification: find consecutive anomaly sub-series (fault runs) per component-KPI within the incident window, filter out isolated noise spikes, and produce compact aggregates (start, end, length, max, severity) to narrow root-cause candidates. We must only use the precomputed global P95 thresholds and the full-file thresholds were already computed.",
