    "instruction": "Using metric.csv and the previously computed global P95 per (cmdb_id,kpi_name), filter metric rows to the incident window 2020-05-31 02:30:00+08 (inclusive) through 2020-05-31 03:00:00+08 (exclusive). For each (cmdb_id,kpi_name) that has at least one row with value > global_p95, identify consecutive breach runs: sort breached timestamps and group consecutive minutes where adjacent timestamps differ by exactly 60 seconds. For each run compute: start_timestamp (Asia/Shanghai), end_timestamp (Asia/Shanghai), run_length_in_minutes, max_value_in_run, global_p95, severity = (max_value_in_run - global_p95)/global_p95. Filter runs to keep only those with run_length_in_minutes >= 2 OR severity > 0.5. Return a compact table of up to top 20 runs sorted by severity descending with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, run_length_in_minutes, start_timestamp, end_timestamp, max_value_in_run, global_p95, severity. Also return the total number of runs after filtering."
